WEBVTT

00:11.792 --> 00:12.834
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:12.917 --> 00:14.709
Your father's been missing
for about two weeks.

00:15.667 --> 00:19.250
He wrote me. I have
a secret legacy, a birthright.

00:20.041 --> 00:22.625
The place he wants me to go,
it's in Lovecraft Country.

00:22.709 --> 00:23.667
♪ (INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:24.083 --> 00:26.333
Well, I've heard a few tales
about travelers being attacked

00:26.417 --> 00:27.542
in the surrounding woods.

00:28.375 --> 00:30.041
They don't like outsiders
at all.

00:31.083 --> 00:32.750
MAN: Come on. Come on.

00:37.625 --> 00:38.792
You're a long way from home.

00:39.041 --> 00:40.417
This is just a misunderstanding.

00:40.875 --> 00:41.875
(GROWLING)

00:42.000 --> 00:43.041
What was that?

00:43.417 --> 00:44.709
OFFICER: Keep your guns on 'em.

00:44.792 --> 00:46.125
-(MONSTER GROWLS)
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)

00:52.166 --> 00:54.959
(PIERCING WHISTLE)

01:00.166 --> 01:02.417
MAN: We've been expecting you,
Mr. Freeman.

01:04.792 --> 01:05.959
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:07.000 --> 01:08.375
[TV static drones]

01:08.458 --> 01:10.917
[bright tone]

01:12.792 --> 01:15.500
- ♪ Well, we're movin' on up ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

01:15.583 --> 01:18.500
- ♪ To the East Side ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

01:18.583 --> 01:23.250
- ♪ To a deluxe apartment
in the sky ♪

01:23.333 --> 01:26.041
♪ Movin' on up ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

01:26.125 --> 01:29.125
- ♪ To the East Side ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

01:29.208 --> 01:31.250
- ♪ We finally got a piece ♪

01:31.333 --> 01:34.542
♪ Of the pie ♪

01:34.625 --> 01:37.250
♪ Fish don't fry
in the kitchen ♪

01:37.333 --> 01:40.041
♪ Beans don't burn
on the grill ♪

01:40.125 --> 01:42.625
♪ Took a whole lotta tryin' ♪
- [cackling]

01:42.709 --> 01:45.542
- ♪ Just to get up that hill ♪

01:45.625 --> 01:47.792
♪ Now we're up
in the big leagues ♪

01:47.875 --> 01:50.417
♪ Gettin' our turn at bat ♪

01:50.500 --> 01:52.959
♪ As long as we live,
it's you and me, baby ♪

01:53.041 --> 01:54.625
♪ There ain't
nothin' wrong with that ♪

01:54.709 --> 01:57.458
♪ Well, we're movin' on up ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

01:57.542 --> 02:00.291
- ♪ To the East Side ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

02:00.375 --> 02:05.083
- ♪ To a deluxe apartment
in the sky ♪

02:05.166 --> 02:07.917
♪ Movin' on up ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

02:08.000 --> 02:10.959
- ♪ To the East Side ♪
- ♪ Movin' on up ♪

02:11.041 --> 02:13.417
- ♪ We finally got a piece ♪

02:13.500 --> 02:17.709
♪ Of the pie ♪

02:21.500 --> 02:23.458
[monster chittering]

02:23.542 --> 02:26.500
[eerie music]

02:26.583 --> 02:33.542
♪ ♪

02:41.417 --> 02:44.333
[menacing music]

02:44.417 --> 02:51.458
♪ ♪

02:53.583 --> 02:56.583
[bell ringing]

02:57.709 --> 02:58.709
[door latch clicks]

03:00.166 --> 03:01.834
- Is that an alarm?

03:01.917 --> 03:03.875
- Nobody seems alarmed.

03:03.959 --> 03:05.625
- You got your own library,
too?

03:05.709 --> 03:08.667
They got Blackwood,
Hodgson, Clark Ashton Smith.

03:08.750 --> 03:11.166
I could stay in there
reading all day.

03:11.250 --> 03:13.125
- I wonder if that's the point.

03:13.208 --> 03:15.500
[door latch clicks]

03:15.583 --> 03:18.041
- Good Lord, Letitia.

03:18.125 --> 03:19.458
- You like?

03:19.542 --> 03:22.083
Found it and a lot more
in the wardrobe.

03:22.166 --> 03:24.500
Tried on a few
before settling on this.

03:24.583 --> 03:26.000
- And they all fit?

03:26.083 --> 03:28.166
- Like a glove.

03:28.250 --> 03:30.667
- [clears throat]

03:30.750 --> 03:33.417
Mr. Freeman,
the elder Mr. Freeman,

03:33.500 --> 03:36.583
and Miss Lewis,

03:36.667 --> 03:38.166
I'm glad you all
were able to freshen up

03:38.250 --> 03:40.667
before the chime
of the lunch bell.

03:40.750 --> 03:44.709
Nothing to be alarmed about.

03:44.792 --> 03:47.333
If you'll allow me
to escort you to the veranda.

03:47.417 --> 03:50.083
[uneasy music]

03:50.166 --> 03:57.166
♪ ♪

04:02.125 --> 04:03.750
- William, is it?

04:03.834 --> 04:06.917
- That is correct, Mr. Freeman.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.542
I wasn't sure
that you would remember.

04:08.625 --> 04:10.834
You were a little...
out of sorts

04:10.917 --> 04:14.792
when you arrived this morning.

04:14.875 --> 04:18.291
- When's my father
expected to return from Boston?

04:18.375 --> 04:20.875
- I am afraid that I have
already told you everything

04:20.959 --> 04:24.083
that I have been made privy to.

04:24.166 --> 04:26.291
He left to see the lawyer
with Miss Braithwhite

04:26.375 --> 04:28.333
two nights ago.

04:28.417 --> 04:30.125
She gave no instructions
on when they would return.

04:30.208 --> 04:31.959
- But we were expected?

04:32.041 --> 04:35.041
- She made it very clear
that I was to look out for you,

04:35.125 --> 04:37.959
treat you like family
while you wait.

04:38.041 --> 04:42.625
♪ ♪

04:42.709 --> 04:44.291
- What hotel
are they at in Boston?

04:44.375 --> 04:45.792
I want to call and check in.

04:45.875 --> 04:47.792
- Unfortunately,
that's going to be impossible.

04:47.875 --> 04:50.125
Upon inheriting the land,
Samuel Braithwhite

04:50.208 --> 04:52.667
decided to use it
for his summer home,

04:52.750 --> 04:54.458
and never installed
telephone lines

04:54.542 --> 04:56.125
so as not to be disturbed
by the business

04:56.208 --> 04:57.792
that hounds him
most of the year.

04:57.875 --> 05:00.625
- And what business
does he have with my father?

05:00.709 --> 05:02.125
- I don't know,

05:02.208 --> 05:05.166
and it wouldn't be
my place to say.

05:05.250 --> 05:07.417
- Is that
the Samuel Braithwhite

05:07.500 --> 05:08.917
you've been speaking of?

05:09.000 --> 05:11.125
- That is a distant cousin
of Samuel's,

05:11.208 --> 05:12.625
Ardham's founder,

05:12.709 --> 05:15.291
and the original owner
of the lodge,

05:15.375 --> 05:17.291
Titus Braithwhite.
- Hmm.

05:17.375 --> 05:19.834
- He built this retreat so that
he and his fellow lodge members

05:19.917 --> 05:23.166
could dine in private.

05:23.250 --> 05:25.083
He was quite
an extraordinary man.

05:25.166 --> 05:28.125
- He must've been to build
such an impressive home.

05:28.208 --> 05:30.625
How did he come
about his fortune?

05:30.709 --> 05:33.458
- Shipping.
- That's code for slaves.

05:33.542 --> 05:37.000
- Titus was known
to be notoriously kind

05:37.083 --> 05:38.500
to those who worked for him.

05:38.583 --> 05:40.041
- Hmm.

05:40.125 --> 05:42.500
- Many mourned
after the great fire.

05:42.583 --> 05:43.625
- There was a fire?

05:43.709 --> 05:45.834
- What we are standing in
is a replica

05:45.917 --> 05:48.125
of the original lodge,
which burned down

05:48.208 --> 05:52.834
during the autumnal equinox,
1833.

05:52.917 --> 05:55.500
It was an unfortunate accident
that killed Titus

05:55.583 --> 05:58.500
and everyone else inside.

05:58.583 --> 06:02.333
Well, almost everyone.

06:02.417 --> 06:05.333
[eerie music]

06:05.417 --> 06:12.417
♪ ♪

06:17.417 --> 06:19.875
Mr. Braithwhite has called
a gathering of lodge members

06:19.959 --> 06:22.917
who are expected to arrive
for a celebratory dinner.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.959
Until then,
you have the run of the lodge.

06:26.041 --> 06:27.333
- After lunch,
we'd like to take a walk

06:27.417 --> 06:30.542
around the village.

06:30.625 --> 06:32.542
That won't be a problem,
will it?

06:32.625 --> 06:35.417
- No, as long as you return
in time for dinner.

06:38.125 --> 06:39.709
Now, if you need anything else,

06:39.792 --> 06:41.583
anything at all,
just ring the bell,

06:41.667 --> 06:43.375
and the butler
will come running.

06:43.458 --> 06:45.375
- I thought
you were the butler.

06:45.458 --> 06:46.333
- No.

06:46.417 --> 06:47.542
No, I'm just
a close personal friend

06:47.625 --> 06:50.417
to Christina Braithwhite.

06:50.500 --> 06:51.709
- Does that silver Bentley
out front

06:51.792 --> 06:54.333
belong to Miss Braithwhite?

06:54.417 --> 06:56.542
- Yes.

06:56.625 --> 06:58.542
But she has many cars.

07:05.542 --> 07:07.458
- When have you ever showed up
to a white man's house

07:07.542 --> 07:10.041
uninvited and he didn't try
to get you out in 2.5 seconds?

07:10.125 --> 07:11.625
- They want to keep us here.

07:11.709 --> 07:14.375
- I don't want to find out why.

07:14.458 --> 07:16.041
I know Pops
is around here somewhere.

07:16.125 --> 07:17.750
- He's definitely not
in Boston.

07:17.834 --> 07:19.834
[bell ringing]

07:22.834 --> 07:25.375
- What?
I need salt.

07:25.458 --> 07:27.959
You know white folks
don't be seasoning their food.

07:28.041 --> 07:29.750
- What's wrong with you?
[door latch clicks]

07:29.834 --> 07:30.792
First, you parading around here

07:30.875 --> 07:32.750
like you on the--
- Tic. Tic.

07:32.834 --> 07:34.834
- Thank you.

07:36.166 --> 07:39.000
- How can you even eat
after what happened last night?

07:39.083 --> 07:41.750
- Because I...

07:41.834 --> 07:44.792
[suspenseful music]

07:44.875 --> 07:47.917
I...

07:48.000 --> 07:50.166
don't remember what happened.

07:50.250 --> 07:56.291
♪ ♪

07:56.375 --> 07:59.417
- You serious?

07:59.500 --> 08:01.458
Hey, Leti, we were attacked.

08:01.542 --> 08:04.375
- By the sheriff?
- By monsters.

08:04.458 --> 08:06.333
- What monsters?
- Eight-foot-tall beasts

08:06.417 --> 08:09.375
with razor-sharp teeth
that can bite a man's head off.

08:10.542 --> 08:11.792
Uncle George?

08:11.875 --> 08:13.125
- Last thing I remember
is cleaning up

08:13.208 --> 08:15.250
in the lodge this morning.

08:15.333 --> 08:17.458
- No, you...you got knocked
out in the fight,

08:17.542 --> 08:18.458
but you gotta remember

08:18.542 --> 08:20.000
the monsters
attacking the cabin.

08:20.083 --> 08:22.375
- What cabin?
- The cabin in the woods.

08:22.458 --> 08:23.709
Uncle George,
they had us surrounded.

08:23.792 --> 08:25.709
Then there was that high-pitched
whistle that called them off.

08:25.792 --> 08:26.792
- Like a dog whistle?

08:26.875 --> 08:27.959
- No, Leti,
it wasn't a dog whistle.

08:28.041 --> 08:29.792
These weren't dogs.

08:29.875 --> 08:31.667
Remember, you crashed Woody

08:31.750 --> 08:33.207
into the cabin
right after I shot the sheriff.

08:33.291 --> 08:35.332
- You shot the sheriff?
- I had to shoot the sheriff.

08:35.417 --> 08:37.332
Yeah! He got bit
by one of those things.

08:37.417 --> 08:38.542
They're like vampires.

08:38.625 --> 08:41.875
Uncle George, remember,
you quoted Dracula.

08:41.958 --> 08:43.625
You remember that?

08:43.708 --> 08:45.875
- We're being watched.

08:45.959 --> 08:49.542
♪ ♪

08:49.625 --> 08:52.458
Sit down.

08:52.542 --> 08:55.458
[foreboding string music]

08:55.542 --> 08:58.333
♪ ♪

08:58.417 --> 09:01.333
- We need to find Pop
and get the hell out of here.

09:01.417 --> 09:03.917
Take Leti and search the lodge.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.333
I'ma check down in the village.

09:05.417 --> 09:07.250
- Mm-mm.
We are not splitting up.

09:07.333 --> 09:08.709
- She's right.

09:08.792 --> 09:11.083
We stay together
and be discreet.

09:11.166 --> 09:14.583
They've been treating us
real nice right now,

09:14.667 --> 09:17.208
and we don't want to give them
a reason to do otherwise.

09:17.291 --> 09:20.250
[distressed music]

09:20.333 --> 09:27.291
♪ ♪

09:34.458 --> 09:37.458
You said the car was crashed.

09:39.500 --> 09:41.458
- It was.

09:41.542 --> 09:42.750
This can't be Woody.

09:42.834 --> 09:45.417
- Well,
my camera's in the front seat.

09:45.500 --> 09:47.125
- And the back window's
busted out.

09:47.208 --> 09:50.500
- [clears throat]
[dramatic musical sting]

09:52.500 --> 09:54.875
The elder Mr. Freeman,
your keys.

09:54.959 --> 09:56.208
- How'd this get here?

09:56.291 --> 09:57.750
- I found it
parked on the other side

09:57.834 --> 09:58.750
of the bridge
leading into the village.

09:58.834 --> 10:00.208
- That's impossible.

10:00.291 --> 10:02.041
It was crashed.

10:02.125 --> 10:04.458
- I assure you, I drove it up
just like I found it.

10:04.542 --> 10:07.083
- What?

10:07.166 --> 10:08.583
What aren't you telling us?

10:08.667 --> 10:10.917
- There was quite a bit
of blood in the front seats,

10:11.000 --> 10:14.542
but I had the butler
wash it out.

10:14.625 --> 10:15.583
I assume that was the trouble

10:15.667 --> 10:17.959
that you ran into
on the road last night.

10:22.458 --> 10:25.208
- Let's go.

10:25.291 --> 10:28.250
[foreboding music]

10:28.333 --> 10:35.333
♪ ♪

10:43.250 --> 10:45.959
[shutter snaps]

10:46.041 --> 10:48.291
- What are you doing?
Come on.

10:48.375 --> 10:49.792
- Can I ask you something?

10:49.875 --> 10:51.959
[children laughing]

10:52.041 --> 10:54.583
Did Atticus kill
a lot of people in the war?

10:54.667 --> 10:57.500
- Anything he did was
for the service of his country.

10:57.583 --> 11:01.250
- I know, but Woody wasn't
crashed like he said it was.

11:01.333 --> 11:02.667
It was covered in blood.

11:02.750 --> 11:03.917
- None of this makes any sense.

11:04.000 --> 11:06.583
Why can't either of us remember
anything that happened?

11:06.667 --> 11:08.166
- I'm trying.

11:08.250 --> 11:11.125
This monster business?

11:11.208 --> 11:13.333
A lot of soldiers came back
from the war with shell shock.

11:13.417 --> 11:14.375
What if whatever--

11:14.458 --> 11:17.709
- This isn't shell shock.

11:17.792 --> 11:19.333
I know what I saw last night.
I know.

11:19.417 --> 11:21.375
- Hold on, hold on.
We're just concerned about you.

11:21.458 --> 11:22.458
That's all.

11:22.542 --> 11:24.083
What you said happened
doesn't make any sense.

11:24.166 --> 11:25.625
- You know what else doesn't?

11:25.709 --> 11:27.792
A bookshelf full
of your favorite books, hmm?

11:27.875 --> 11:30.709
A wardrobe full of clothes
in Leti's exact size.

11:30.792 --> 11:34.875
Can you ex--
[high-pitched whistle trills]

11:34.959 --> 11:38.166
That's the whistle
that called off the monsters.

11:38.250 --> 11:41.166
[suspenseful music]

11:41.250 --> 11:43.709
[high-pitched whistle trills]

11:45.291 --> 11:47.333
Hey!

11:47.417 --> 11:50.041
You! Were you in the woods
last night?

11:50.125 --> 11:51.083
- Who the hell are you?

11:51.166 --> 11:52.875
[dogs barking]

11:52.959 --> 11:54.208
- What's that whistle for?
- Tic, stop!

11:54.291 --> 11:55.458
- Not the dogs.
- Tic!

11:55.542 --> 11:57.208
- Answer the question!
What's that whistle really for?

11:57.291 --> 11:58.709
- I'm sorry, ma'am.

11:58.792 --> 12:00.875
- Stop.
- Please call them dogs off.

12:00.959 --> 12:04.208
- My dogs aren't the ones
that need to be on a leash.

12:04.291 --> 12:07.291
- We're guests
of Mr. Braithwhite.

12:09.291 --> 12:11.834
[dogs panting passively]

12:14.458 --> 12:17.208
- You don't look like the type
to be Braithwhite's guests.

12:17.291 --> 12:20.041
- Are you the sheriff?
- What makes you think that?

12:20.125 --> 12:21.709
- That's the jail, right?

12:21.792 --> 12:23.041
I mean,
it's the only stone building

12:23.125 --> 12:24.750
I've seen
in the entire village.

12:24.834 --> 12:29.083
- [laughs]
[dogs barking]

12:29.166 --> 12:30.083
[barking stops]

12:30.166 --> 12:32.333
[uneasy music]

12:32.417 --> 12:35.083
- We get animals
coming in the village.

12:35.166 --> 12:38.291
They break into the cottages...

12:38.375 --> 12:40.458
but not in here.

12:40.542 --> 12:42.250
[dogs lapping hungrily]

12:42.333 --> 12:45.333
- I heard about your grizzlies
in the surrounding area.

12:45.417 --> 12:47.709
- No, no grizzlies,

12:47.792 --> 12:49.709
just black bears.

12:49.792 --> 12:54.250
But the blacks are bad enough.
They're smart.

12:54.333 --> 12:56.542
They're not smart  smart.

12:56.625 --> 12:57.959
They're beasts,

12:58.041 --> 13:00.625
but they're clever enough
to cause mischief.

13:00.709 --> 13:02.917
♪ ♪

13:03.000 --> 13:06.250
And they're persistent,

13:06.333 --> 13:11.291
always sticking their noses
where they don't belong.

13:11.375 --> 13:14.375
- Mm-hmm.

13:14.458 --> 13:18.625
- I suggest you all
head back on up to the lodge

13:18.709 --> 13:20.291
before the sun goes down.

13:20.375 --> 13:23.125
You don't want to miss dinner.

13:23.208 --> 13:26.208
- Thank you, ma'am.

13:36.875 --> 13:40.291
The inside of that silo's
got a stone foundation,

13:40.375 --> 13:43.500
which means
a dungeon-like basement.

13:43.583 --> 13:45.500
- And all that barking,
you wouldn't be able

13:45.583 --> 13:49.291
to hear someone if they were
screaming for help.

13:49.375 --> 13:51.417
- That's where
they're keeping Pop.

13:51.500 --> 13:56.542
♪ ♪

13:56.625 --> 13:57.583
When we get back
to the lodge,

13:57.667 --> 13:59.000
we gonna have to make
a quick getaway.

13:59.083 --> 14:00.500
- Mm-hmm.
- Be gone before they start

14:00.583 --> 14:01.834
burning crosses.

14:01.917 --> 14:03.583
- Need something faster
than Woody.

14:03.667 --> 14:04.709
- You gonna have to steal it.

14:04.792 --> 14:06.583
- I can handle that.

14:06.667 --> 14:09.333
- Something told me you could.

14:09.417 --> 14:11.417
Uncle George?

14:14.542 --> 14:17.000
What is it?

14:17.083 --> 14:18.875
- A recollection,
something your mother

14:18.959 --> 14:23.208
told me years ago
about her ancestors.

14:23.291 --> 14:27.041
- She never told me or Pop
anything about her people...

14:27.125 --> 14:28.959
but she told you?

14:29.041 --> 14:30.959
- I think
she was just ashamed of it.

14:31.041 --> 14:35.333
She told me her great-ancestor
was a slave named Hanna

14:35.417 --> 14:39.208
and that she escaped her
master's house after a fire.

14:39.291 --> 14:42.500
[uneasy music]

14:42.583 --> 14:45.041
- The secret birthright
Pop wrote about.

14:45.125 --> 14:47.583
- Titus Braithwhite

14:47.667 --> 14:50.709
was known to
be notoriously "kind"

14:50.792 --> 14:52.792
to his slaves.

14:56.625 --> 14:59.208
- Hanna ran
through these woods pregnant.

14:59.291 --> 15:01.583
She was a brave woman.

15:01.667 --> 15:03.500
[rustling sound]

15:06.000 --> 15:07.208
What the hell is that?

15:07.291 --> 15:08.709
[earth rumbling]

15:08.792 --> 15:11.875
[screaming]

15:11.959 --> 15:15.875
[monsters snarling]

15:15.959 --> 15:18.917
[intense music]

15:19.000 --> 15:23.250
♪ ♪

15:23.333 --> 15:25.750
[high-pitched whistle trills]

15:25.834 --> 15:29.291
[dramatic music]

15:31.125 --> 15:34.125
[whistle blowing]
[monsters chittering]

15:38.000 --> 15:40.417
- Escort the younger
Mr. Freeman to my father's lab,

15:40.500 --> 15:43.166
and make sure our other guests
stay in their rooms.

15:55.458 --> 15:59.250
- Why are we c-covered in dirt?

15:59.333 --> 16:02.583
- I...I don't know.

16:02.667 --> 16:04.458
It happened again, didn't it?

16:04.542 --> 16:06.417
- Shut it!
Let's move!

16:06.500 --> 16:09.417
[mysterious music]

16:09.500 --> 16:15.458
♪ ♪

16:15.542 --> 16:18.458
[man screaming]

16:18.542 --> 16:24.500
♪ ♪

16:26.709 --> 16:30.709
- [hollering]

16:33.750 --> 16:36.667
[eerie music]

16:36.750 --> 16:43.750
♪ ♪

16:49.917 --> 16:52.917
- We were walking
in the woods.

16:55.250 --> 16:58.250
I remember...

17:05.625 --> 17:10.583
If Tic's related,
then Montrose was just bait.

17:19.750 --> 17:22.709
[dramatic music]

17:22.791 --> 17:29.792
♪ ♪

17:33.000 --> 17:34.959
[mechanism clacks]

17:41.125 --> 17:44.041
[suspenseful music]

17:44.125 --> 17:50.834
♪ ♪

17:55.458 --> 17:58.417
[dramatic music]

17:58.500 --> 18:05.500
♪ ♪

18:13.208 --> 18:16.000
"Order of the Ancient Dawn."

18:19.166 --> 18:22.083
[suspenseful music]

18:22.166 --> 18:28.834
♪ ♪

18:35.834 --> 18:38.583
[eerie music]

18:38.667 --> 18:43.500
♪ ♪

18:43.583 --> 18:46.291
- He's darker than I expected.

18:46.375 --> 18:48.959
[groans]

18:49.041 --> 18:52.417
- Let me help you.
- I'm fine.

18:52.500 --> 18:55.750
[groans]

19:05.875 --> 19:08.250
This here is one
of my favorite paintings.

19:08.333 --> 19:13.291
The artist, Josef Tannhauser,
entitled it "Genesis 2:19."

19:13.375 --> 19:15.166
Are either of you
familiar with the verse?

19:15.250 --> 19:17.375
♪ ♪

19:17.458 --> 19:19.166
- "And out of the ground,
the Lord God

19:19.250 --> 19:20.625
"formed every beast
of the field

19:20.709 --> 19:22.083
"and every fowl of the air

19:22.166 --> 19:23.417
"and brought them unto Adam

19:23.500 --> 19:24.959
"to see what
he would call them,

19:25.041 --> 19:27.834
"and whatsoever Adam
called every living creature,

19:27.917 --> 19:29.834
that was the name thereof."

19:29.917 --> 19:31.542
- In Tannhauser's conception,

19:31.625 --> 19:35.125
this act of naming is more than
a simple picking of labels.

19:35.208 --> 19:37.792
Adam is sharing in creation,

19:37.875 --> 19:41.041
assigning each creature
its final form

19:41.125 --> 19:43.667
and its station
in the hierarchy of nature.

19:43.750 --> 19:46.834
What does that mean, Christina?

19:46.917 --> 19:50.417
What did Adam do?

19:53.291 --> 19:54.709
- He put everything
in its place.

20:00.959 --> 20:03.500
- At the dawn of time,
just for a moment,

20:03.583 --> 20:05.500
everything was where

20:05.583 --> 20:09.500
and as it should be...

20:09.583 --> 20:13.083
from God to man to woman,

20:13.166 --> 20:16.166
down to the lowliest
wriggling creature.

20:18.667 --> 20:21.500
It was Nirvana.

20:21.583 --> 20:25.000
- Then that stupid, meddlesome,
troublemaking bitch Eve

20:25.083 --> 20:28.709
brought entropy and death.

20:28.792 --> 20:30.959
What was an elegant hierarchy

20:31.041 --> 20:34.417
became a mess
of tribes and nations.

20:34.500 --> 20:37.000
Of course, it didn't
really happen that way.

20:37.083 --> 20:41.083
Biblical literalism
is for the simple.

20:42.792 --> 20:46.417
But I'm sure everyone
in this room is aware of that.

20:46.500 --> 20:49.375
- It's still a useful parable
for both of you.

20:49.458 --> 20:51.750
- I'm guessing you're God

20:51.834 --> 20:53.667
in this useful parable.

20:56.500 --> 20:59.083
- I'm Adam.

20:59.166 --> 21:01.583
And I've worked
a very long time

21:01.667 --> 21:03.458
to return to paradise.

21:03.542 --> 21:06.083
♪ ♪

21:06.166 --> 21:09.792
My daughter seems to believe
you can help in my aims,

21:09.875 --> 21:13.709
but as you can see,
there's little we agree on.

21:13.792 --> 21:16.709
- Then why don't you just tell
me where I can find my father?

21:16.792 --> 21:18.250
All right, and I'll leave you
and the rest of--

21:18.333 --> 21:21.917
- I don't want to see him again
until the ceremony at dawn.

21:22.000 --> 21:24.917
[suspenseful music]

21:25.000 --> 21:30.625
♪ ♪

21:30.709 --> 21:34.667
- You must have
so many questions.

21:34.750 --> 21:37.125
- Why bother?

21:37.208 --> 21:39.041
None of the other ones
I asked have been answered,

21:39.125 --> 21:41.792
not by your father,
or--what's the other guy?

21:41.875 --> 21:43.542
He your boyfriend?

21:43.625 --> 21:45.250
- William.

21:45.333 --> 21:50.083
And yes, he is a boy
and a friend sometimes.

21:50.166 --> 21:53.500
My father may have looked
feeble upstairs,

21:53.583 --> 21:57.041
but he, along with the rest
of the lodge members arriving,

21:57.125 --> 22:01.959
can be very dangerous enemies
to have.

22:02.041 --> 22:04.917
You should think
about making some friends.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.125
Not all us white folks
are out to get you.

22:07.208 --> 22:08.500
- I have enough friends.

22:08.583 --> 22:11.375
- Are you sure about that?

22:13.041 --> 22:14.458
Your uncle and Leti
seem to think

22:14.542 --> 22:17.834
you lost your marbles
in the war.

22:17.917 --> 22:20.000
- That's because you did
something to make them forget.

22:20.083 --> 22:23.333
- Did something?
How vague.

22:23.417 --> 22:25.291
- It's a spell.

22:25.375 --> 22:27.834
It's a spell.

22:27.917 --> 22:29.000
It seems the KKK isn't just

22:29.083 --> 22:30.792
calling themselves
"grand wizards" anymore.

22:30.875 --> 22:33.542
- My father and his associates
would never fraternize

22:33.625 --> 22:35.375
with the Klan.

22:35.458 --> 22:36.875
They're too poor.

22:36.959 --> 22:38.500
And the spell
wasn't specifically

22:38.583 --> 22:40.041
for your companions,

22:40.125 --> 22:42.542
rather, anyone who encounters
our little guard dogs

22:42.625 --> 22:43.625
and lives to tell about it.

22:43.709 --> 22:47.667
- You want to be friends?
Fine.

22:47.750 --> 22:50.542
That's gonna take actions,
not just promises.

22:50.625 --> 22:52.583
- And getting you out
of trouble in Simmonsville,

22:52.667 --> 22:54.166
as well as last night,
wasn't enough?

22:54.250 --> 22:55.208
- We're in trouble now.

22:55.291 --> 22:57.750
- I can't take you
to your father.

22:57.834 --> 23:02.250
- Then remove the spell
on Leti and my uncle...

23:02.333 --> 23:04.250
friend.

23:04.333 --> 23:07.250
[tense music]

23:07.333 --> 23:09.417
♪ ♪

23:09.500 --> 23:11.875
- Done.

23:11.959 --> 23:14.041
- [screams]
- Tic!

23:14.125 --> 23:15.625
[mysterious whoosh]
- [grunts]

23:15.709 --> 23:19.333
[screaming
and banging on doors]

23:19.417 --> 23:21.875
- Open this fucking door!

23:21.959 --> 23:24.917
Let me out!

23:25.000 --> 23:26.375
- Tic!

23:26.458 --> 23:28.458
[screams]

23:30.458 --> 23:33.750
- Miss Braithwhite, it's time.

23:33.834 --> 23:35.041
[doors rattling]

23:35.125 --> 23:37.208
- Let me out!
Let me out!

23:37.291 --> 23:39.250
[cow lowing]

23:39.333 --> 23:41.917
[driving string music]

23:42.000 --> 23:43.792
- You wanted us to tell you
when there was a breach.

23:43.875 --> 23:45.959
- Yes, thank you.

23:47.709 --> 23:50.625
[dramatic music]

23:50.709 --> 23:56.709
♪ ♪

23:56.792 --> 23:57.917
[cow groans]

23:58.000 --> 24:02.000
- [groaning]

24:05.667 --> 24:07.417
- Pull harder!

24:07.500 --> 24:08.542
[cow groaning]

24:08.625 --> 24:11.625
[creature chittering]

24:16.834 --> 24:19.750
[gentle music]

24:19.834 --> 24:25.333
♪ ♪

24:25.417 --> 24:29.458
- Miss Braithwhite,
you done this before?

24:29.542 --> 24:31.625
- [quietly] No.

24:31.709 --> 24:36.417
It's my first time.

24:36.500 --> 24:39.500
[monsters chittering]

24:39.583 --> 24:44.125
[dramatic music]

24:44.208 --> 24:46.208
[door rattles]

24:48.250 --> 24:50.166
[latch clicking]

24:50.250 --> 24:53.000
[suspenseful music]

24:53.083 --> 24:54.166
- [yells]

24:54.250 --> 24:55.291
- Leti.

24:55.375 --> 24:58.500
- Oh, Tic, Tic, I'm so sorry.
I remember now.

24:58.583 --> 25:01.166
- I know, I know.
- I should've believed you.

25:01.250 --> 25:03.500
- Let's sit down for a second.
- No, we gotta get out of here.

25:03.583 --> 25:06.291
- Leti, Leti,
they got us trapped, okay?

25:06.375 --> 25:08.166
But I'm gonna figure a way out.
I promise.

25:08.250 --> 25:11.250
- Okay.
- Come sit with me.

25:24.750 --> 25:27.834
- The Bible is full of demons

25:27.917 --> 25:30.333
and monsters.

25:30.417 --> 25:33.000
They're just stories.

25:33.083 --> 25:36.000
They have to be because...

25:36.083 --> 25:39.542
- "Even though I walk
through the darkest valley,

25:39.625 --> 25:43.625
I will fear no evil,
for you are with me."

25:45.667 --> 25:47.417
- I said that last night.

25:47.500 --> 25:49.083
- Just before doing
the bravest thing

25:49.166 --> 25:52.500
I've ever seen to save us.

25:52.583 --> 25:57.041
- I can't believe
I even remember that verse.

25:57.125 --> 26:01.542
Last time I said it,
I was a kid, and...

26:01.625 --> 26:04.625
- And what?

26:04.709 --> 26:09.041
- Terrified.

26:09.125 --> 26:12.125
My mom would leave me
by myself all the time.

26:15.250 --> 26:19.208
Say she was going to church.

26:19.291 --> 26:23.208
But even then,
I knew that was a lie.

26:23.291 --> 26:24.333
She always came home,

26:24.417 --> 26:29.000
usually with some new man
hanging on her arm.

26:31.500 --> 26:34.625
Till one day, she didn't,

26:34.709 --> 26:38.375
and a week went by.

26:38.458 --> 26:42.083
I was so scared that
she wasn't gonna come back.

26:42.166 --> 26:43.250
And I was little.

26:43.333 --> 26:47.792
I--I didn't--I didn't know
how to take care of myself.

26:51.875 --> 26:55.083
I sat...

26:55.166 --> 26:56.542
in the window
of that boarding house

26:56.625 --> 26:59.000
every day...

27:02.166 --> 27:06.166
And said that verse like
a prayer for her to come back.

27:08.417 --> 27:11.417
The one I could remember
from Sunday school.

27:11.500 --> 27:14.417
[dramatic music]

27:14.500 --> 27:21.000
♪ ♪

27:21.083 --> 27:24.458
- I'm never going
to abandon you.

27:24.542 --> 27:27.500
[tender music]

27:27.583 --> 27:34.542
♪ ♪

27:43.917 --> 27:50.959
♪ ♪

27:55.250 --> 27:58.208
[ominous music]

27:58.291 --> 28:05.250
♪ ♪

28:21.583 --> 28:23.583
[light tapping]

28:25.583 --> 28:29.583
[faint noises]

28:35.792 --> 28:38.959
[gun cocks, gunshots]

28:41.166 --> 28:44.792
[both grunting]

28:47.458 --> 28:50.250
- [yells]

28:53.959 --> 28:55.208
Ji-ah, stop!

28:55.291 --> 28:56.750
I don't want to hurt you!

28:56.834 --> 28:58.542
[both grunting]

28:58.625 --> 29:01.542
[dramatic music]

29:01.625 --> 29:08.625
♪ ♪

29:10.792 --> 29:13.792
[soft R&B music]

29:13.875 --> 29:16.417
♪ ♪

29:16.500 --> 29:18.500
- Dora?

29:25.166 --> 29:28.125
- ♪ At the end of a rainbow ♪

29:28.208 --> 29:32.875
- This isn't real.
You're dead.

29:32.959 --> 29:35.750
- ♪ At the end of a story ♪

29:35.834 --> 29:39.750
- Dance with me anyway.

29:39.834 --> 29:44.250
- ♪ But our love
has a treasure ♪

29:44.333 --> 29:47.917
♪ Our hearts
can always spend ♪

29:48.000 --> 29:49.583
♪ And it has a story
without any end ♪

29:49.667 --> 29:53.000
[both grunting]

29:55.542 --> 29:57.291
- [groans]

29:57.375 --> 30:01.250
[both grunting]

30:01.333 --> 30:03.542
- [shouting language of Adam]

30:05.542 --> 30:08.792
- What are you thinking about?

30:08.875 --> 30:10.458
- "The House
on the Borderland."

30:10.542 --> 30:12.625
- [laughs]

30:12.709 --> 30:15.583
You do love your stories.

30:15.667 --> 30:17.917
What's this one about?

30:18.000 --> 30:19.917
- A man who finds
a mysterious home

30:20.000 --> 30:23.000
in the Plain of Silence,

30:23.083 --> 30:28.333
where he fights
humanoid pig-like creatures

30:28.417 --> 30:31.125
before he goes
to the Sea of Sleep,

30:31.208 --> 30:36.375
where he reunites
with his long-lost love.

30:36.458 --> 30:37.750
- Mm.

30:39.542 --> 30:42.625
Do the lovers
stay together forever?

30:42.709 --> 30:45.208
- Yes...

30:45.291 --> 30:47.667
but only because the house
collapses upon them.

30:47.750 --> 30:49.166
- [growls]

30:49.250 --> 30:50.875
- I'm not gonna...

30:50.959 --> 30:52.000
[groans]

30:52.083 --> 30:53.000
[both grunting]

30:53.083 --> 30:57.291
- ♪ At the end of a highway ♪

30:57.375 --> 30:59.000
- [yells]

30:59.083 --> 31:02.208
[both grunting]

31:07.417 --> 31:09.458
- I was thinking about you.

31:09.542 --> 31:10.542
- Mm.

31:10.625 --> 31:14.208
- And Montrose.

31:14.291 --> 31:16.667
Tulsa.

31:16.750 --> 31:18.250
[laughs]

31:18.333 --> 31:21.041
How we used to drink
soda pop on your porch

31:21.125 --> 31:24.583
and play that "what if" game.

31:24.667 --> 31:29.041
What if you could go
anywhere in the world?

31:29.125 --> 31:31.208
What if you could only eat
one thing

31:31.291 --> 31:33.667
for the rest of your life?

31:33.750 --> 31:37.709
What if...
magic were real?

31:37.792 --> 31:40.834
- Montrose wanted
super strength.

31:40.917 --> 31:42.333
- [laughs]

31:42.417 --> 31:44.542
And you wanted to fly.

31:44.625 --> 31:49.083
- ♪ And you are only mine ♪

31:49.166 --> 31:53.583
- That could all
be possible now.

31:53.667 --> 31:57.667
You could actually fly
with your children.

32:02.000 --> 32:04.959
[uneasy music]

32:05.041 --> 32:12.000
♪ ♪

32:18.625 --> 32:19.917
- You're not real.

32:20.000 --> 32:23.709
- Uh, uh, Tic, wait.

32:25.667 --> 32:26.542
Wait, no, no.
Stop.

32:26.625 --> 32:29.875
[both grunting]

32:36.500 --> 32:37.917
[snake hisses]

32:38.000 --> 32:41.041
- [yelling]

32:47.750 --> 32:49.959
[bone snaps]

32:50.041 --> 32:52.959
[eerie music]

32:53.041 --> 33:00.041
♪ ♪

33:02.709 --> 33:06.709
[murmurs and laughter]

33:18.166 --> 33:22.125
[dramatic music]

33:22.208 --> 33:24.625
- What's Braithwhite's
daughter doing here?

33:24.709 --> 33:27.875
- He's out of the Michigan
chapter, isn't he?

33:27.959 --> 33:30.333
[overlapping chatter]

33:30.417 --> 33:31.834
- I heard Samuel has something

33:31.917 --> 33:33.709
very special
planned for dinner.

33:33.792 --> 33:38.792
[bell ringing]

33:51.792 --> 33:54.333
- I hope
you all had a nice rest.

33:54.417 --> 33:57.792
Dinner will be served
in 15 minutes.

33:57.875 --> 34:00.834
The attire is black tie only,

34:00.917 --> 34:02.500
and unfortunately,
Miss Lewis,

34:02.583 --> 34:05.375
it is also men only.

34:05.458 --> 34:06.875
However, it is
a beautiful night

34:06.959 --> 34:08.875
to dine on the veranda.

34:08.958 --> 34:11.667
I will return shortly
to provide escort.

34:18.417 --> 34:22.291
- You okay?

34:24.625 --> 34:27.542
- Who'd they make you see?

34:27.625 --> 34:29.333
- Doesn't matter.

34:29.417 --> 34:33.500
They're just trying
to get inside our heads.

34:33.583 --> 34:36.083
- Something happened
in the war.

34:36.166 --> 34:37.083
Something bad.

34:37.166 --> 34:39.208
- Don't.

34:39.291 --> 34:41.750
You know who you are.

34:41.833 --> 34:46.667
You...were a good boy.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.583
And you're even a better man.

34:48.667 --> 34:52.667
Don't you ever let them
make you question yourself.

34:55.750 --> 34:59.208
That's how they win.

34:59.291 --> 35:02.125
They want to make us crazy,

35:02.208 --> 35:04.417
terrorize us,

35:04.500 --> 35:07.750
make us scared.

35:07.834 --> 35:11.625
But Letitia fucking Lewis
don't get scared,

35:11.709 --> 35:14.083
do she?

35:14.166 --> 35:17.291
- No, sir.
- No, that's right.

35:17.375 --> 35:21.917
Now, I come across something

35:22.000 --> 35:24.583
that just might

35:24.667 --> 35:28.291
get us out of here.

35:28.375 --> 35:31.291
[chamber music playing]

35:31.375 --> 35:38.375
♪ ♪

35:50.000 --> 35:51.792
- Don't mind the others.

35:51.875 --> 35:52.959
Just because
they don't want you here

35:53.041 --> 35:57.041
doesn't mean
you're not supposed to be.

36:03.542 --> 36:06.500
[ominous music]

36:06.583 --> 36:10.542
♪ ♪

36:10.625 --> 36:14.208
- We all know
the true meaning of sacrifice.

36:14.291 --> 36:16.250
Every man in this room

36:16.333 --> 36:19.542
has made an offering
to push the world forward,

36:19.625 --> 36:21.625
a wayward world
we have dedicated

36:21.709 --> 36:23.667
our lives to righting.

36:23.750 --> 36:26.875
Our founder, Titus Braithwhite,
was a son of a son,

36:26.959 --> 36:28.667
and we follow in his image,

36:28.750 --> 36:33.000
just as he followed
in the first son's.

36:33.083 --> 36:36.834
As Adam gave of his rib
to create Eve,

36:36.917 --> 36:39.792
so did Titus give of himself

36:39.875 --> 36:43.709
to empower the founding members
of the Order.

36:43.792 --> 36:47.208
Tonight, on the precipice
of great progress,

36:47.291 --> 36:52.041
I honor him
by giving of myself.

36:52.125 --> 36:54.875
[disquieting music]

36:54.959 --> 36:58.750
♪ ♪

36:58.834 --> 36:59.917
- Don't eat that.

37:00.000 --> 37:03.709
- Tomorrow will truly be
the dawn of a new era.

37:03.792 --> 37:05.333
Thank you all
for coming to witness--

37:05.417 --> 37:07.542
- No need to thank us.

37:07.625 --> 37:11.917
We didn't want to be here.

37:12.000 --> 37:14.208
I understand
y'all belong to a club

37:14.291 --> 37:18.041
called the Order
of Ancient Dawn.

37:18.125 --> 37:21.333
I happened across your bylaws
earlier this evening.

37:21.417 --> 37:23.709
[crowd murmuring]

37:23.792 --> 37:27.208
Now, I got some experience
with fraternal societies,

37:27.291 --> 37:31.041
being a part of
Prince Hall Freemasons myself.

37:31.125 --> 37:34.291
Anybody know
who Prince Hall was?

37:34.375 --> 37:35.959
He was an abolitionist
who joined

37:36.041 --> 37:39.125
the Massachusetts militia
to fight for independence,

37:39.208 --> 37:41.458
and he wanted to join
the local Freemasons,

37:41.542 --> 37:45.417
but, Tic, remind me
why he wasn't allowed in.

37:45.500 --> 37:48.000
- Because he was a colored man.

37:48.083 --> 37:50.458
- I was not surprised
to learn from your bylaws

37:50.542 --> 37:53.291
that your order wouldn't have
admitted Prince Hall, either,

37:53.375 --> 37:54.583
but then I kept reading,

37:54.667 --> 38:00.000
and I found there's a loophole.

38:00.083 --> 38:03.417
Men who are direct descendants
of Titus

38:03.500 --> 38:05.208
are automatically members.

38:05.291 --> 38:07.583
In fact, they're not just
any old members.

38:07.667 --> 38:11.834
They're what's called
sons among sons,

38:11.917 --> 38:13.667
and as you all know,

38:13.750 --> 38:15.375
they can give orders to other,

38:15.458 --> 38:19.125
regular old members.

38:19.208 --> 38:21.000
And seeing
as I believe my nephew

38:21.083 --> 38:23.291
might just be
the last blood heir

38:23.375 --> 38:25.083
of Titus Braithwhite...

38:25.166 --> 38:28.166
[shocked murmuring]

38:29.166 --> 38:31.834
- I want everybody
except Samuel

38:31.917 --> 38:33.834
to get up...

38:33.917 --> 38:35.917
and get the fuck out.

38:50.000 --> 38:54.291
Gentlemen...

38:54.375 --> 38:57.417
that's an order.

39:03.583 --> 39:06.500
[dramatic music]

39:06.583 --> 39:13.583
♪ ♪

39:18.750 --> 39:21.583
I order you
to return my father to me.

39:25.709 --> 39:27.625
- [sighs]

39:27.709 --> 39:30.625
[disquieting music]

39:30.709 --> 39:37.709
♪ ♪

39:48.750 --> 39:52.208
- I am not a zealot,
Mr. Freeman.

39:52.291 --> 39:55.917
The limits of my belief
in tradition and ceremony

39:56.000 --> 39:59.750
stop at the fact that
the others believe it.

39:59.834 --> 40:02.208
Titus used the Book of Names
to spell his body

40:02.291 --> 40:03.875
to be more powerful,

40:03.959 --> 40:06.709
and you're a reservoir
of that power,

40:06.792 --> 40:08.709
diluted, no doubt,

40:08.792 --> 40:10.041
and also tainted somewhat,

40:10.125 --> 40:14.625
but still useful
for the work I have to do.

40:16.250 --> 40:18.041
Do not mistake useful

40:18.125 --> 40:21.750
with indispensable.

40:21.834 --> 40:24.625
[dramatic music]

40:24.709 --> 40:26.041
- Pop!

40:36.000 --> 40:37.959
- This is his.

40:39.667 --> 40:41.458
[gun cocks]

40:41.542 --> 40:42.917
- Just like I thought.

40:43.000 --> 40:45.458
Bunch of dumb animals

40:45.542 --> 40:47.417
don't know enough
to stop fighting

40:47.500 --> 40:50.041
once they're already snared.

40:50.125 --> 40:53.291
Hmm? My dogs will get
a nice treat tonight.

40:53.375 --> 40:54.750
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

40:54.834 --> 40:56.834
[Dell grunting]

40:59.000 --> 41:02.583
- I got the car.
Where's Montrose?

41:04.542 --> 41:06.792
- "Count of Monte Cristo."

41:06.875 --> 41:09.125
- Pop's favorite book?

41:09.208 --> 41:12.166
[melancholy soul music]

41:12.250 --> 41:16.458
♪ ♪

41:16.542 --> 41:21.291
- Help me.
- ♪ You ain't ever gonna fly ♪

41:21.375 --> 41:24.667
♪ No place big enough
for holding ♪

41:24.750 --> 41:26.792
♪ ♪

41:26.875 --> 41:30.750
♪ All the tears
you're gonna cry ♪

41:30.834 --> 41:34.750
♪ 'Cause your mama's name
was lonely ♪

41:34.834 --> 41:39.417
♪ ♪

41:39.500 --> 41:43.166
♪ And he called you
little sorrow ♪

41:43.250 --> 41:47.834
♪ 'Cause you'll never
love again ♪

41:47.917 --> 41:52.834
♪ So why you wanna fly,
Blackbird? ♪

41:52.917 --> 41:55.667
♪ ♪

41:55.750 --> 41:58.834
♪ You ain't ever gonna fly ♪

41:58.917 --> 42:01.917
- [panting]

42:03.208 --> 42:05.917
-  Hey, Montrose.

42:07.917 --> 42:10.000
- What the hell
y'all doing here?

42:10.083 --> 42:11.000
- We're here to save you.

42:11.083 --> 42:13.125
- I saved my damn self.

42:13.208 --> 42:15.959
I ain't need
y'all coming for me.

42:16.041 --> 42:17.834
- You wrote for me to come.

42:17.917 --> 42:20.333
- Boy, we ain't spoken
over five damn years,

42:20.417 --> 42:21.834
and you fight me on everything.

42:21.917 --> 42:23.709
Obviously, I didn't think
you were stupid enough

42:23.792 --> 42:25.709
to show up 'cause I wrote
a letter under duress.

42:25.792 --> 42:27.041
- You don't need to talk
to him like that.

42:27.125 --> 42:29.542
- I'll talk to my son
however the hell I want to.

42:29.625 --> 42:31.959
- Can we get the fuck
out of here, please?

42:35.417 --> 42:38.583
[engine turns over]

42:38.667 --> 42:40.208
- They have lodges
all over the country.

42:40.291 --> 42:41.834
This one's called
the Sons of Adam,

42:41.917 --> 42:43.709
founded by Titus Braithwhite

42:43.792 --> 42:45.875
after he discovered what
they call the Book of Names.

42:45.959 --> 42:47.542
- Yeah, the Necronomicon.

42:47.625 --> 42:48.875
- No,
that's the book of dead names.

42:48.959 --> 42:51.041
This is the book of life,
transformation, genesis.

42:51.125 --> 42:54.250
They're obsessed with figuring
out the spell for immortality.

42:54.333 --> 42:56.709
A failed attempt is what
burned the original lodge,

42:56.792 --> 42:59.709
killing everyone inside--

42:59.792 --> 43:02.709
[dramatic music]

43:02.792 --> 43:09.834
♪ ♪

43:14.500 --> 43:17.417
[Marilyn Manson's
"Killing Strangers"]

43:17.500 --> 43:22.917
♪ ♪

43:23.000 --> 43:27.250
- ♪ This world
doesn't need no opera ♪

43:27.333 --> 43:31.125
♪ We're here
for the operation ♪

43:31.208 --> 43:35.583
♪ We don't need
a bigger knife ♪

43:35.667 --> 43:39.250
♪ A bigger knife ♪

43:39.333 --> 43:41.291
♪ Cause we got guns ♪

43:41.375 --> 43:43.291
♪ We got guns ♪

43:43.375 --> 43:45.375
♪ You better run ♪

43:45.458 --> 43:48.917
♪ You better run,
you better run ♪

43:49.000 --> 43:52.083
- [groans]

43:52.166 --> 43:53.417
[gunshot]
[screams]

43:53.500 --> 43:54.917
- Leti!

43:55.000 --> 43:58.959
- [gasping]

43:59.041 --> 44:03.291
- Leti, I got you.
I got you.

44:03.375 --> 44:08.000
- Help me.
- Let me see, let me see.

44:08.083 --> 44:10.500
You're okay.
You're okay.

44:10.583 --> 44:12.291
I got you.
- [whimpers]

44:12.375 --> 44:14.625
- I got you.

44:14.709 --> 44:17.667
Uncle George!
Uncle George!

44:17.750 --> 44:20.083
[gunshot]

44:20.166 --> 44:21.166
- Christina!

44:21.250 --> 44:23.625
Christina, help us, please!

44:23.709 --> 44:26.834
Please, please.

44:26.917 --> 44:30.959
- Tic.

44:31.041 --> 44:33.500
[coughs]

44:33.583 --> 44:36.166
- Leti? Leti, stay awake.

44:36.250 --> 44:38.875
Stay awake, okay?
Stay awake.

44:38.959 --> 44:40.500
Leti, stay awake.
Stay awake!

44:40.583 --> 44:42.458
Stay awake, please.

44:42.542 --> 44:44.500
Please, please.
[mutters]

44:44.583 --> 44:47.542
[mournful music]

44:47.625 --> 44:54.583
♪ ♪

44:59.458 --> 45:02.542
- Since you are
a son among sons,

45:02.625 --> 45:04.166
I will give you a choice

45:04.250 --> 45:07.333
of who else survives
your error in judgment.

45:07.417 --> 45:10.375
[dramatic music]

45:10.458 --> 45:15.792
♪ ♪

45:15.875 --> 45:17.875
- Wait!
[gunshot]

45:17.959 --> 45:21.667
- ♪ We're killing strangers ♪

45:21.750 --> 45:25.709
♪ We're killing strangers ♪

45:25.792 --> 45:28.208
♪ We're killing strangers ♪

45:28.291 --> 45:30.709
♪ So we don't kill ♪

45:30.792 --> 45:34.709
♪ The ones that we love ♪

45:34.792 --> 45:37.208
♪ ♪

45:37.291 --> 45:40.750
♪ Love! ♪

45:40.834 --> 45:44.375
♪ Love! ♪

45:44.458 --> 45:46.959
♪ Love ♪

45:50.125 --> 45:52.750
- So what's gonna happen
in the ceremony?

45:52.834 --> 45:57.458
- My father intends to open
a door to the Garden of Eden,

45:57.542 --> 46:00.542
to a time
when man was immortal.

46:00.625 --> 46:04.583
He believes he'll step
through it into eternal life.

46:04.667 --> 46:08.417
- Those ambitions didn't go
too well for Titus, did they?

46:08.500 --> 46:10.125
- Challenging entropy
is perilous work,

46:10.208 --> 46:13.083
and the Language of Adam
is a tricky thing to get right.

46:13.166 --> 46:17.083
Many men have suffered greatly
trying to wield it.

46:17.166 --> 46:18.875
But the spelled blood
of the man

46:18.959 --> 46:21.917
who wielded it best might
just give my father's spell

46:22.000 --> 46:25.083
the advantage it needs.

46:25.166 --> 46:28.333
- So that's why
you brought me here.

46:28.417 --> 46:29.917
To help a father
who clearly doesn't give

46:30.000 --> 46:32.083
two shits about you.

46:32.166 --> 46:36.417
After all, it's not called
the Daughters of Adam, is it?

46:39.417 --> 46:42.333
- The things they've done...

46:42.417 --> 46:45.834
it's unforgivable.

46:45.917 --> 46:48.625
We still come running
when they need help.

46:48.709 --> 46:49.959
It's pathetic.

46:50.041 --> 46:53.792
And we call it family
to make it seem okay?

46:53.875 --> 46:56.834
[dramatic music]

46:56.917 --> 47:01.417
♪ ♪

47:01.500 --> 47:03.959
- You didn't
have to drag them into it.

47:04.041 --> 47:07.333
- I didn't bring two of them.

47:07.417 --> 47:10.625
[Letitia gasping]

47:10.709 --> 47:13.750
[warm music]

47:13.834 --> 47:18.500
♪ ♪

47:18.583 --> 47:21.333
For what it's worth, my father
is a gentleman of his word,

47:21.417 --> 47:24.041
and he will heal
your uncle as well.

47:24.125 --> 47:27.792
- Once I've willingly
participated in the ceremony.

47:27.875 --> 47:30.375
I got it.

47:30.458 --> 47:33.583
Let's get on with it.

47:36.417 --> 47:38.959
- I could never earn
one of these,

47:39.041 --> 47:42.000
no matter how hard I tried,

47:42.083 --> 47:43.542
and you get one
for doing nothing

47:43.625 --> 47:46.208
other than being born a man.

47:46.291 --> 47:48.917
- Not even a white man at that.

47:55.375 --> 47:58.375
- What I know is, our destinies
are not decided

47:58.458 --> 48:01.583
by our fathers or grandfathers

48:01.667 --> 48:02.750
or, in your case,

48:02.834 --> 48:06.250
great-great-great-great
grandfather.

48:06.333 --> 48:08.458
The smallest,
most inconsequential thing

48:08.542 --> 48:10.208
can take you on a new course.

48:10.291 --> 48:14.375
You just have to see it...

48:14.458 --> 48:18.250
and seize it.

48:18.333 --> 48:21.083
[suspenseful music]

48:21.166 --> 48:28.166
♪ ♪

48:32.959 --> 48:36.166
- [panting]

48:36.250 --> 48:39.166
[ominous music]

48:39.250 --> 48:46.291
♪ ♪

48:53.542 --> 49:00.500
♪ ♪

49:06.792 --> 49:09.792
[sobbing]

49:11.500 --> 49:15.166
[muffled crying]

49:20.166 --> 49:23.583
- You should try
breaking that window.

49:23.667 --> 49:25.625
- We're not leaving here
without you, George.

49:25.709 --> 49:27.458
- At least try to get
the girl out of here.

49:27.542 --> 49:29.125
- [scoffs]

49:29.208 --> 49:32.625
She doesn't seem like
the type to tell what to do.

49:32.709 --> 49:34.375
Reminds me of Dee.

49:34.458 --> 49:36.583
- How come you never drew
with her?

49:36.667 --> 49:39.125
You used to draw all the time.

49:39.208 --> 49:40.458
- No, I didn't.

49:40.542 --> 49:42.792
You getting senile
in your old age.

49:42.875 --> 49:46.667
- Every summer,
you used to draw this colorful

49:46.750 --> 49:48.583
welcome sign,

49:48.667 --> 49:50.625
go down to the bus station,

49:50.709 --> 49:53.834
and cheer on
all the Negro league players

49:53.917 --> 49:57.834
as they rode in
for training camp.

49:57.917 --> 49:59.917
Why'd you stop?

50:02.208 --> 50:05.667
- 'Cause of Daddy's right hook.

50:05.750 --> 50:09.750
Caught me down at that station
the summer before high school.

50:11.250 --> 50:13.375
Beat the black off my ass.

50:17.542 --> 50:21.667
- I didn't know that.

50:21.750 --> 50:24.667
You were brimming
with love as a boy,

50:24.750 --> 50:27.709
despite being afforded
so little.

50:27.792 --> 50:30.291
If I ever made you feel...

50:34.625 --> 50:37.125
There's nothing wrong
with loving that much.

50:37.208 --> 50:39.125
- You need to shut up and rest.

50:39.208 --> 50:41.959
- That's the problem.

50:42.041 --> 50:44.166
I've been shutting up
for far too long,

50:44.250 --> 50:45.542
and hurt those I love.

50:45.625 --> 50:50.208
You, Hippolyta, Tic.

50:50.291 --> 50:52.542
I want you to show him
more of that love

50:52.625 --> 50:54.375
I know is in you before...

50:54.458 --> 50:58.875
it's...too late.

50:58.959 --> 51:00.875
- How many times
I gotta tell you?

51:00.959 --> 51:02.375
I don't need your advice
when it comes

51:02.458 --> 51:04.375
to raising my son.

51:04.458 --> 51:06.709
- He might not be yours.

51:06.792 --> 51:09.709
[suspenseful music]

51:09.792 --> 51:15.375
♪ ♪

51:15.458 --> 51:18.709
- I don't care if you got
a bullet in your gut.

51:18.792 --> 51:20.041
We settled that
a long time ago.

51:20.125 --> 51:21.834
You shut your fucking mouth.

51:21.917 --> 51:24.375
- I know, I know.

51:24.458 --> 51:27.125
We agreed
we wouldn't speak of it,

51:27.208 --> 51:30.917
but I have to now.

51:31.000 --> 51:33.959
You might be all Tic has left.

51:34.041 --> 51:38.417
♪ ♪

51:38.500 --> 51:40.125
- We have a poem here.

51:40.208 --> 51:41.750
It's called
"Whitey on the Moon."

51:41.834 --> 51:43.709
[laughter]

51:43.792 --> 51:48.041
And, uh, it was inspired--

51:48.125 --> 51:52.333
it was inspired by
some whiteys on the Moon,

51:52.417 --> 51:55.250
so I want to give credit
where credit is due.

51:55.333 --> 51:56.709
[laughter]

51:56.792 --> 51:58.417
All right.

51:58.500 --> 52:01.083
Let's see.

52:01.166 --> 52:02.375
[upbeat drum music]

52:02.458 --> 52:05.375
- [chanting
in Language of Adam]

52:05.458 --> 52:10.125
♪ ♪

